Assistant to the President John Brennan spoke to President Ali Abdallah Saleh of Yemen to welcome President Saleh's initiative to resolve the political crisis in Yemen. Brennan emphasized the need for representatives of all sectors of the Yemeni opposition to respond constructively to President Saleh's call for dialogue. He stated that both the government and the opposition are responsible for achieving a peaceful resolution of the crisis. Brennan also highlighted the importance of an open and transparent process that addresses the legitimate concerns of the Yemeni people for the country's progress. President Saleh expressed his hope that the opposition would engage in dialogue with the government and assured that violence would not be used against peaceful demonstrators.